item.title: [HBASE-8637] IntegrationTestBigLinkedListWithChaosMonkey uses the wrong table name
item.description: IntegrationTestBigLinkedListWithChaosMonkey creates a table named IntegrationTestBigLinkedListWithChaosMonkey but when inserting data it doesn't insert any data into it.

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: Elliot, how did you test this? This is on distributed setup, right? Do you have steps to repro?

I've run the Integration test using the following command several times successfully.


mvn failsafe:integration-test -Dit.test=IntegrationTestBigLinkedListWithChaosMonkey

so on a real cluster running: 

hbase org.apache.hadoop.hbase.IntegrationTestsDriver -r IntegrationTestBigLinkedListWithChaosMonkey
